Crack the eggs and ease them into a bowl containing 1/2 cup water. Prick the yolks and cover the bowl with plastic wrap. Microwave for 1-1/2 to 2 minutes or until the outsides of the yolks are firm. Prepare the hollandaise sauce according to the package directions. Toast the English muffin. Place 1 tablespoon sauce on one half muffin; top with one slice of cooked bacon, add one egg, and spoon 1 tablespoon sauce over the top. Serve with a broiled grapefruit half: Top with 1-1/2 tablespoons brown sugar and broil for 5 minutes.